<TITLE> Channel 1 staff seek resumption </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com)  Employees of private TV station Channel 1 demanded the resumption of transmission on Thursday after it was knocked off air two days ago. They made the demand in a human chain formed in front of the National Press Club for one and a half hours starting at 11:30am. The demonstrators said since their fate was tied with the channel they wanted an end to the uncertainty. They are not concerned about the problems of the owner, the employees said and added that they would hold a rally on the same venue on May 2. The private TV station was knocked off air on Tuesday by the regulators over allegation of breach of regulation. The director of the station on Wednesday pleaded for a second chance and said that they would move the court over the decision to suspend its transmission. The station started transmission on Jan 24, 2006 during the regime of BNP-led government. b
